\id 1TH - Plain English Version
\h 1 Thessalonians
\toc2 1 Thessalonians
\toc1 Paul’s 1st Letter to the Thessalonians
\mt1 The 1st letter that Paul wrote to the Christians at Thessalonica
\mt2 (The book in the Holy Bible called \bk 1 Thessalonians\bk*)
\imt1 About this letter
\ip Paul wrote this letter about 2,000 years ago, about 20 years after Jesus went back to heaven, and it is now in the Holy Bible.
\ip God sent Paul to lots of countries and lots of towns to tell people about Jesus. One of those towns was Thessalonica (see Acts 17:1-9). It was a big town in the country called Greece, where the Greek people come from, and it is still there today. Sometimes people now call that town Salonica. \fig This is what Thessalonica town looks like now|src="dragos-gontariu-unsplash.tif" size="col" ref="1:0"\fig*
\ip When Paul went to Thessalonica some people believed in Jesus and became Christians, but others didn’t like what he was saying, and they made trouble for him. So he could not stay there very long. Soon after that he sent his friend Timothy back to Thessalonica to find out how those new Christians were going, and to help them be strong for Jesus. After Timothy came back and told him how they were going, Paul wrote them this letter. Paul’s 2 friends, Silas and Timothy, they helped him write this letter. This was the 1st letter that Paul wrote to them. He wrote them another letter about 6 months later.
\ip In this letter Paul wrote about the time when Jesus will come back from heaven, and he said other important things too. So today we have to take notice of what Paul wrote to the Christians at Thessalonica.
\cl Chapter
\c 1
\p 
\v 1 \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G2532"\w* \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* letter \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w from|strong="G1515"\w* me. Silas \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Timothy|strong="G5095"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w here|strong="G1722"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* me, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w helping|strong="G2532"\w* me write \w this|strong="G3588"\w* letter.
